            <title>[KAFKA-14717] KafkaStreams can&apos; get running if the rebalance happens before StreamThread gets shutdown completely</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-14717</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I noticed this issue when tracing &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-7109&quot; title=&quot;KafkaConsumer should close its incremental fetch sessions on close&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;KAFKA-7109&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;KAFKA-7109&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;StreamThread closes the consumer before changing state to DEAD. If the partition rebalance happens quickly, the other StreamThreads can&apos;t change KafkaStream state from REBALANCING to RUNNING since there is a PENDING_SHUTDOWN StreamThread&lt;/p&gt;</description>
